annotation.TEXT: Whoa, fireballs!
Space-time rewind count: 2
Pfft... That was a failed jump all right. But fortunately, even the lavalavalava teleports me back to start instead of killing me.
Yeah, I was ready for Mavericks that time.
Dr. Robotnik's Mean Bean Machine? ...No, that's something entirely different.
Wait, what? The game booted me back to the title screen?! But, I wasn't done with HackLand yet! There were still three other prizes for me to claim! Hold on a moment...

Well, it looks like I'll need a total of 15 Happy Coins to claim all of these items, assuming I can acquire the coins fast enough before everything's sold out. (Looks like all of the 2-coin and 4-coin prizes are already sold out.)
Perry? What are you doing here? Shouldn't you be pursuing science?
Space-time rewind count: 4
I'd better move very carefully, and wait a split-second after releasing a direction before I try to move in a different direction.
Oh, man! There's the balloons! Pop them, quick!
Hey there, duders and dudettes, and welcome to La Grande Finale of Hack 2!
BGM: BONUS!, by Red Chameleon (Also used in Info)
Oh, what?
Alright, with this Doubler Voucher, my 3 Happy Coins are now worth 6, so let's go buy that ticket!
Yeah, looks like that's gonna be the case.
Huh. Sounds interesting...
Oh, man. This HackLand place sounds fun!
Yes, I've won my second Happy Coin!
Miss.
Whoa, I got very close to the floor there!
D'oh, that one got away.
BGM: Super Mario Bros. 3 - Game Over
I totally whiffed on that one. (But, looking back, I hit an offscreen balloon with that toss.)
Oh, I totally want that adorable Dino Torch plushie!
Alright, and with my third Happy Coin, I can now claim that Dino Torch plushie!
Everybody is still saying the same stuff.
"Tick." Graze +1. Yep, I can slip under that first Podoboo just by standing still. The less I have to jump, the better.
Maybe this area is constantly checking my horizontal speed, and once I'm moving, if I come to a stop (like by hitting the side of that block), I fail.
Oh, I see. Yeah, it wouldn't be very sporting to fight Mr. Bowser when he's sick. Alright, so let's check out those festivities...

But, apparently, I guess if I press up or down immediately as I left go of left or right, my horizontal momentum is preserved as I start moving vertically. Man, these controls are about as bad as fence climbing in SMW NES!
Maybe if I jump around on the tents and poles, I'll find something...
Okay, right now, I'm intentionally trying to move diagonally, and it's only allowing the horizontal direction when I push down+right or down+left.
Barf! I missed that jump. But, why did the game warp me out? It looked like I was gonna land on the gray platform below me...
Huh, the edge of the log here is a slope. Well, whatever. Let's get that Dino Torch plushie now!
BGM: Bugs Bunny Birthday Blowout - Bonus Round (Also used in Dope)
Okay, I need two more Happy Coins to qualify for one of the lesser prizes. I'm comin' for ya, Dino Torch plushie!
This final level must really be something for this video to be over 18 minutes in length, especially considering how short each of the other levels are!
He must be laughing at the newspaper comics or something.
You can also apparently jump on these poles.

(By the way, I checked this some more later, and it looks like if you're ever not running at max speed anywhere beyond the first screen, you get warped out, so that's why I was warped out the instant I ran off the edge that other time.)
Whoa, what was with the diagonal movement there? I didn't think I was still holding the right arrow key during that descent...
Wait, it's not a plushie, but an actual living Dino Torch? Well, it's still adorable!
Ooh, I like the old-school graphics here. So, I'm controlling this mushroom with the directional buttons. Hmm... What happens if I hit a wall? (For science!)
Daaaaahhhhh!!! Dang! I was doing well that time...
Why can't I enter the door? Do I need to download a ruby keycard first?
Oh, man! So is it going to be similar to that bonus game from Something else, where I'm constantly moving at ludicrous speed?
Yeah, I guess I'm ready.
It can't be nearly as terrifying as that cologne bottle.
Unfortunately, I haven't acquired any Happy Coins yet...
I hope I don't run afoul of the glitchy controls again now...
Alright, I believe I've talked to everyone outside, so let's enter one of these tents, where I assume I'll be able to win some Happy Coins!
Oh, so it was a Tanooki Suit after all! Well, that's fine. The Tanooki Suit is one of the coolest power ups in the Mario series.
Wait, so did I die, or what?
Yep, I've got my 20 exits, so now I can enter the pipe on the right.
Title screen and rewind again? ...Yep.
BGM: Grassland Song, by mariomaniac444 (Also used in Da Bomb and Fly)
Umm... No, I guess not. The game's not forcing me to run at all. Maybe it just contains a lot of jumps that can only be made while running at max speed.
That guy's still pursuing science...

...What? Why did I get warped out that time? I think I was too late in hitting the jump button, and ran off the edge, but I hadn't come to a stop yet. Well, maybe I stepped on an invisible warp tile there, which prevented me from falling into the pit.
Yay, I won a Happy Coin!
Yo, Hammer Bro., what's the deal?
BGM: Super Mario Bros. - Main Theme
Okay, enough nonsense. Let's enter Mario's house now.
BGM: Crusader of Centy - Rafflesia School
Wait, what?! Why would a Tanooki Suit end my game?! It's a useful power up, not something dangerous like that Dino Torch!
Is this gonna send me back to the title screen again, and am I going to rewind back to the prize selection again? ...Yep.
Well, dude, continue working for science!
That looks like a bottle of some sort, and there's a Tanooki Suit here as well. And up top appears to possibly be a ticket. Maybe it's a movie ticket?
Oh, neat. You can jump on the tent, and even slide on it.
Hey there, Luigi. How's it going? ...Wait, dishes? Oh, man...
Ah, this must be where the remaining three Happy Coins are!
BGM: Super Mario Bros. 2 - Boss Defeated
Okay, that was just creepy... I'd rather be roasted by the Dino Torch.
I think I'm going to wait until I've finished VVVVVV's Dimension Open before I begin another Mario hack. But, I'll probably still do some more SMW Challenges in the meantime. See y'all later!
Just one more Happy Coin and I get the Dino Torch plushie! I really hope it's not sold out by the time I get my third Happy Coin!
WHOA!!!
Actually, didn't I do the weird spasm level before the cake level?
Oh, man. There's a big moving wall that I have to wait for here.
At least this reason for not touching the tracks is better than in I think Something else, where Luigi was apparently too dumb to walk on the tracks, or something like that.
That guy's still enjoying the comics...

Alright, so the bottle was clearly bad as well. But, now what? All three of the prizes that I can afford result in my game suddenly ending. There's still the ticket up there, but that requires twice as many Happy Coins as I currently have.
Oh, there's Mario! So, that means...
I don't think I got enough... (Looking back, I hit 8 of them, and missed 4, so there's a little leeway, but not much. In order to win, I can't miss more than 2 balloons.)
Whoa, hello!
That guy's still singing happily...
Oh, what the foodge!
...Carpet stains? I thought you said he was housebroken...
Oh, god... It's cologne? Umm... I don't know if I like where this is going...
Alright, it's final boss time! ...Wait, what?
Barely got those last two.
D'oh! I missed that one!
Oh, I just get booted out of the tent. Alright, let's try this again for realsies now.
Well, at least it looks like I can just keep trying until I succeed.
Don't forget the kiss on the nose and cake in SM64.
I'm almost positive I let go of right when I hit up there...
Whoa, Podoboos! Ack!
...Um... Who are you? Are you from the first "Hack" and I simply forgot? (UPDATE: Yes, I did forget, but he's not from "Hack". He's from SMW 2+3 The Essence Star.)
Man, you gotta be fast for most of these! I hope that there's more than ten balloons total in this area, so that I'm allowed to miss some.
Ow... Bad Dino Torch! You're not supposed to burn your owner!
BGM: RednGreen - Fatal Chase
Also, there's no side exits to this area. I know there's more to this hack. Namely, a way to purchase that ticket, which leads to the real ending, but I forget how to do that...
Okay, seriously! There must be something wrong with the controls there!
...Louie? So, Mario calls him Louie now?
Oh, brother! Hahaha! Well, whatever works!
Alright, I've rewound back to the point just before I claimed the Dino Torch, which I no longer want, because it's apparently evil. I think I'll try out the Tanooki Suit instead.
D'oh! I was able to slip under the first Bowser statue there, but not the second.
Okay, I'm past the part where I failed the first time, but it's getting tricky now!
Umm... Game?
Ooh, those things up there are the prizes?
Oh, what is this...? Perry, you're really creepy. Go away and resume pursuing science.
Whoa! I just barely cleared that last wall! Also, I'm glad I didn't double-hit that pair of ON/OFF blocks earlier!
Mario has a wife and kid back in Brooklyn?
Huh, so if I touch the tracks, I just get warped back to the beginning of this cart ride.
Okay, moving to the right a little bit while slipping under the second Bowser statue worked.
Ooh, I've gotta win me some Happy Coins!
Space-time rewind count: 3
I wonder if I can slip under that first Podoboo... Maybe I'll try that next time if I fail again.
Oh, right! I remember now! Yeah, this will allow me to purchase that ticket!
BGM: Final Fantasy VI - Gogo's Theme
Teddy bear? I thought it was a Tanooki Suit. Well, at least this isn't a live animal that's gonna suddenly end my game and send me to the Underwhere without warning.
Let's see... SMB came out in 1985, and this hack was made in 2013, so it's been 28 years.
Oh, hey there, Bowser and Peach. How's it going? ...Wait, I thought Bowser was sick... So, was he faking his illness all along?
Gah! Maverick Thwomp! ...Oh, so getting hit by an enemy also just resets the ride. I like that the game doesn't actually kill me for failing here!
Wait, I didn't claim the cologne bottle prize on this timeline, since I space-time rewound out of that, so Perry mentioning cologne here doesn't make sense.
Looks like the Yoshi coin counter keeps track of my Happy Coins.
Oh, man! We're starting! And, oh, man! This song's awesome!
Well, that just happened. And suddenly, I'm home, apparently.
Yep, I do believe I am truly done now! So, I hope you all enjoyed watching me play through Hack 2!
So, I've gotta locate three more Happy Coins somehow. Are there any tents or anything that I haven't visited yet?

Uhh... Who is Roth? I don't think that's a name I'm familiar with, unless I'm simply forgetting something... (UPDATE: Roth is also from The Essence Star. In fact, Roth is the purple guy just to the right, and this guy is Perry's grandpa.)
So, I guess this is the true ending, right?
Alright, so for some reason that I can't comprehend, the Tanooki Suit is bad news. Let's try out the bottle, I guess. Is this like those bottles in Zelda games that I can put fairies in?
Oh, freaking heck! I hit the corner of that ON/OFF block, which put a halt to my horizontal movement...
Alright, it's balloon popping time!
